Three things to actually do before this works, and one heads-up:

The SQL has to be run manually against your Supabase project — there's no `migrations/` folder yet, just the flat `schema.sql`/`rls-policies.sql` files, so paste the two new blocks into the SQL Editor in that order. Set both `VITE_PAYSTACK_PUBLIC_KEY` and `PAYSTACK_SECRET_KEY` to a real Paystack **test-mode** key pair first and run a payment end-to-end before anything live touches it — your real public/secret keys go in whichever `.env` actually gets deployed, same as your existing dev/prod split. And redeploy `verify-paystack` after the rewrite.

The heads-up: while in there I confirmed `attachment_reports` also doesn't exist in `schema.sql` — so report *content* (not the payment, the actual generated chapters/submission) has been running on localStorage-only this whole time too, meaning a liaison officer reviewing flagged reports currently can't see them from their own session. That's outside what you asked for today, but it's the natural next thing once finance is live.